/**
 * DeepStarCatalog.ts
 *
 * Deeper Hipparcos-based star catalog, opt-in via Preferences -> Simulation ->
 * "Deeper star catalog". The catalog is the ESA Gaia-archive Hipparcos main
 * catalogue (table public.hipparcos): every star with a visual magnitude
 * vmag <= 7.5, recovered to equatorial coordinates and sorted ascending by
 * magnitude (Sirius first). At 25713 stars it is a ~6x superset of the
 * bundled BrightStarCatalog (mag <= 5.8), so when the preference is enabled it
 * fully replaces the bright-star arrays during rendering.
 *
 * Provenance -- regenerate with:
 *   curl 'https://gea.esac.esa.int/tap-server/tap/sync' \
 *     --data-urlencode 'REQUEST=doQuery' --data-urlencode 'LANG=ADQL' \
 *     --data-urlencode 'FORMAT=csv' \
 *     --data-urlencode 'QUERY=SELECT ra,de,vmag FROM public.hipparcos WHERE vmag<=7.5 AND ra IS NOT NULL AND de IS NOT NULL AND vmag IS NOT NULL ORDER BY vmag ASC'
 * then pack to little-endian Float32 triples (ra/15 -> hours, de deg, vmag).
 *
 * Storage: the packed bytes are embedded as base64 below so the catalog ships
 * in every build mode (including single-file, where copyPublicDir is false and
 * no runtime fetch is possible) and is CSP-safe (no connect-src / data: needed).
 * It is decoded lazily on first access via getDeepStarData so the decode cost
 * is paid only when the preference is turned on.
 */

